{"title_page": "Luka Don\u010di\u0107", "text_new": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Slovenian basketball player}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Luka Don\u010di\u0107\n| image = Luka Don\u010di\u0107 7 Real Madrid Baloncesto Euroleague 20171012.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Don\u010di\u0107 with [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]] in 2017\n| number = 77\n| position = [[Guard (basketball)|Guard]] / [[Small forward]]\n| team = Dallas Mavericks\n| league = [[NBA]]\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 7\n| weight_lbs = 230\n| nationality = Slovenian\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1999|2|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Ljubljana]], Slovenia\n| career_start = 2015\n| career_end = \n| draft_year = 2018\n| draft_round = 1\n| draft_pick = 3\n| draft_team = [[Atlanta Hawks]]\n| years1 = 2015\u20132018\n| team1 = [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]]\n| years2 = {{nbay|2018|start}}\u2013present\n| team2 = [[Dallas Mavericks]]\n| highlights = \n* [[List of NBA All-Stars|NBA All-Star]] ({{nasg|2020}})\n* [[NBA Rookie of the Year]] ({{nbay|2018|end}})\n* [[NBA All-Rookie First Team]] ({{nbay|2018|end}})\n* [[EuroLeague 2010\u201320 All-Decade Team]] (2020)\n* [[EuroLeague]] champion ([[2017\u201318 EuroLeague|2018]])\n* [[EuroLeague MVP]] ([[2017\u201318 EuroLeague|2018]])\n* [[EuroLeague Final Four MVP]] ([[2018 EuroLeague Final Four|2018]])\n* [[All-EuroLeague Team|All-EuroLeague First Team]] ([[2017\u201318 EuroLeague|2018]])\n* 2\u00d7 [[EuroLeague Rising Star]] ([[2016\u201317 EuroLeague|2017]], [[2017\u201318 EuroLeague|2018]])\n* [[Euroscar|Euroscar Player of the Year]] (2019)\n* 3\u00d7 [[Liga ACB]] champion ([[2014\u201315 ACB season|2015]], [[2015\u201316 ACB season|2016]], [[2017\u201318 ACB season|2018]])\n* [[ACB Most Valuable Player Award|Liga ACB MVP]] ([[2017\u201318 ACB season|2018]])\n* [[All-Liga ACB Team|All-Liga ACB First Team]] ([[2017\u201318 ACB season|2018]])\n* 2\u00d7 [[ACB Best Young Player Award|ACB Best Young Player]] ([[2016\u201317 ACB season|2017]], [[2017\u201318 ACB season|2018]])\n* 3\u00d7 [[ACB Best Young Player Award|ACB All-Young Players Team]] ([[2015\u201316 ACB season|2016]]\u2013[[2017\u201318 ACB season|2018]])\n* 2\u00d7 [[Spanish Basketball King's Cup|Spanish King's Cup]] winner ([[2016 Copa del Rey de Baloncesto|2016]], [[2017 Copa del Rey de Baloncesto|2017]])\n* [[Sports Illustrated Sportsperson of the Year|''Sports Illustrated''  Breakout of the Year]] (2019)\n* [[FIBA Intercontinental Cup]] champion ([[2015 FIBA Intercontinental Cup|2015]])\n* [[Euroleague Basketball Next Generation Tournament|EB Next Generation Tournament]] champion ([[2014\u201315 Euroleague Basketball Next Generation Tournament|2015]])\n* [[Euroleague Basketball Next Generation Tournament#Finals|EB Next Generation Tournament MVP]] ([[2014\u201315 Euroleague Basketball Next Generation Tournament|2015]])\n* Minicopa del Rey MVP (2013)\n| nba_profile = luka_doncic\n| bbr = doncilu01\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalSport|Men's [[basketball]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{bk|SLO}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[EuroBasket]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[EuroBasket 2017|2017 Turkey]]|}}\n}}\n'''Luka Don\u010di\u0107''' ({{IPA-sl|\u02c8l\u00f9\u02d0ka \u02c8d\u00f2\u02d0nt\u0283it\u0283|lang}}; born February 28, 1999) is a Slovenian professional [[basketball]] player for the [[Dallas Mavericks]] of the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA) and the [[Slovenia national basketball team|Slovenian national team]].\n\nBorn in [[Ljubljana]], Don\u010di\u0107 shone as a youth player for [[KK Olimpija|Union Olimpija]], before joining the youth academy of the Spanish club, [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]]. He debuted for their senior team in 2015, at age 16, becoming the youngest in club history. Two years later, he led Madrid to the [[2018 EuroLeague Final Four|2018 EuroLeague title]], winning the [[EuroLeague MVP]] as well as the [[EuroLeague Final Four MVP|Final Four MVP]]. Don\u010di\u0107 was also named the [[ACB Most Valuable Player Award|ACB Most Valuable Player]], and won back-to-back [[EuroLeague Rising Star]] and [[ACB Best Young Player Award|ACB Best Young Player]] awards. He was selected to the [[EuroLeague 2010\u201320 All-Decade Team]].\n\nIn 2018, Don\u010di\u0107 declared for the [[2018 NBA draft|NBA draft]] and joined the Dallas Mavericks in the United States.{{refn|group=note|Don\u010di\u0107 was selected by the [[Atlanta Hawks]] with the 3rd pick in the 2018 NBA Draft, but was acquired by the Mavericks in a [[Trade (sports)|draft-day trade]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Amick |last=Sam |title=Mavs, Hawks trade Trae Young, Luka Doncic in draft-night deal |work=USA Today |date=June 21, 2018 |url=https://usatoday.com/story/sports/nba/draft/2018/06/21/2018-nba-draft-trae-young-luka-doncic-swapped-trade/723919002/ |accessdate=October 5, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic traded to Dallas Mavericks after Atlanta Hawks draft him with No. 3 pick in 2018 NBA Draft |publisher=CBS Sports |date=June 21, 2018 |url=https://www.cbssports.com/nba/news/luka-doncic-traded-to-dallas-mavericks-after-atlanta-hawks-draft-him-with-no-3-pick-in-2018-nba-draft/ |accessdate=October 5, 2018}}</ref>}} He was selected unanimously to the [[NBA All-Rookie Team|NBA All-Rookie First Team]] and won [[NBA Rookie of the Year Award|Rookie of the Year]] for the [[2018\u201319 NBA season|2018\u201319 season]]. In his sophomore season, he was selected to his first [[List of NBA All-Stars|NBA All-Star]] game.\n\nA Slovenian international, Don\u010di\u0107 made his senior debut for Slovenia in 2016 at only 17 years of age; he would later be named to the [[FIBA EuroBasket All-Tournament Team#2017 EuroBasket|All-Tournament Team]] after helping his country win its first [[EuroBasket]] title in [[EuroBasket 2017|2017]].\n\n==Early life==\nDon\u010di\u0107 was born in [[Ljubljana]], Slovenia, to Mirjam Poterbin, owner of beauty salons,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Stein |first1=Marc |title=Luka Doncic Is a Sore Loser. He Is Also a Sensation. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/27/sports/luka-doncic-dallas-mavericks.html |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=March 3, 2019 |date=February 27, 2019}}</ref> and [[Sa\u0161a Don\u010di\u0107]], a basketball coach and former basketball player.<ref name=slam/><ref name=\"enaa\">{{cite news | url= http://lifestyle.enaa.com/ljudje/nusa-senk-zmesala-kosarkarja-sasa-doncica.html | title = Nu\u0161a \u0160enk zme\u0161ala ko\u0161arkarja Sa\u0161a Don\u010di\u010da |trans-title=Nusa Senk captivated basketball player Sasa Doncic | publisher = lifestyle.enaa.com | date = September 18, 2008 | accessdate = February 2, 2017 | language = Slovenian }}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107's mother is Slovenian and his father is Slovenian of Serbian descent.<ref name=\"b92_sasa\">{{cite news | url= http://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2017&mm=03&dd=10&nav_id=1238747 | title = Don\u010di\u0107: Luka Zvezda\u0161? Nasledio je to od mene |trans-title=Doncic: Luka a fan of Crvena Zvezda? He inherited that from me | publisher = [[B92]] | date = March 10, 2017 | accessdate = October 25, 2017 | language = Serbian }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Staji\u0107 |first1=Sa\u0161a M. |title=Ekskluzivno, Sa\u0161a Don\u010di\u0107: Otac najve\u0107eg talenta u Evropi zna ne\u0161to \u0161to \u0107e odu\u0161eviti svakog Srbina! |url=https://www.espreso.rs/sport/eurobasket/181975/eksluzivno-sasa-doncic-otac-najveceg-talenta-u-evropi-zna-nesto-sto-ce-oduseviti-svakog-srbina-video |publisher=Espreso |accessdate=October 1, 2018 |language=Serbian |date=September 14, 2017}}</ref> His parents filed for divorce in 2008, with custody and legal guardianship being granted to his mother.<ref name=\"enaa\"/><ref name=\"ekipa1\">{{cite news | url= http://ekipa24.si/clanek/kosarka/reprezentancna-kosarka/567d5e0813259/spanski-potni-list | title = \u0160panski potni list? |trans-title=Spanish passport? |last1=Zavr\u0161nik|first1=Jurij| publisher = [[Ekipa (Slovenia)|Ekipa]] | date =December 25, 2015| accessdate =February 2, 2017| language = Slovenian }}</ref>\n\nAccording to his family, Don\u010di\u0107 first touched a basketball when he was seven months old, and by age one, he was frequently playing with a miniature hoop in his room.<ref name=slam/><ref name=schmitz/> He played a variety of sports in his childhood, including [[association football|football]], which he later quit after growing too tall.<ref name=\"motherseyes\">{{cite web |last1=Aravantinos |first1=Dionysis |title=Luka Doncic through his mother's eyes! |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/trademarks/601550/story-week-luka-doncic-mothers-eyes/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=June 6, 2018 |date=January 25, 2018}}</ref> At age seven, he began playing organized basketball at primary school in Ljubljana.<ref name=schmitz>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/20668236/there-never-nba-draft-prospect-slovenia-luka-doncic |title=There's never been an NBA draft prospect like Luka Doncic |first=Mike |last=Schmitz |publisher=[[ESPN]] |date=September 18, 2017 |accessdate=September 18, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"borntoplay\">{{cite web|last1=West|first1=Andy|title=Conversation with Luka Doncic: 'I was born to play basketball'|url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/899lwl554gpgofk6/conversation-with-luka-doncic-i-was-born-to-play-basketball|publisher=[[EuroLeague]]|accessdate=April 21, 2018|date=October 11, 2017}}</ref> His opponents at the time were up to ten years old, as Don\u010di\u0107 reflected: \"I was always training and playing with older kids who had much more experience than me. Many of them were bigger and faster than me too, so I had to beat them with my brain.\"<ref name=borntoplay/> He admired Greek basketball player [[Vassilis Spanoulis]] from his early teenage years, stating that he was \"enchanted\" by him.<ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic: \"I got enchanted by Spanoulis\" |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/euroleague/561446/doncic-got-enchanted-spanoulis/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=July 2, 2018 |date=November 25, 2017}}</ref> He wore the number 7 at Real Madrid in honor of Spanoulis.<ref>{{cite AV media |people= |date=March 14, 2018 |title=Luka Doncic: The Future Is Now |series=The Insider EuroLeague Documentary Series  |trans-title= |medium=Video |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HVIl9zTTgFA |access-date=January 3, 2019 |minutes=22 |publisher=[[EuroLeague]]}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 also grew up admiring American basketball player, [[LeBron James]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cash |first1=Meredith |title=Luka Doncic waited outside the Lakers' locker room after game for a jersey from his idol, LeBron James |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/luka-doncic-waited-postgame-for-idol-lebron-james-jersey-2018-11 |publisher=Business Insider |accessdate=16 December 2019 |date=1 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Youth career==\n;Union Olimpija\nWhen Don\u010di\u0107 was eight, his father started playing for his hometown club [[KK Olimpija|Union Olimpija]], and Olimpija Basketball School coach Grega Brezovec invited Luka to practice with players of his age.<ref name=schmitz/><ref name=\"scottdavis\">{{cite web|last1=Davis|first1=Scott|title=Potential No. 1 NBA draft pick was so good at age 8 that coaches moved him up an age group after watching him play for 16 minutes|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/luka-doncic-too-good-slovenia-team-age-8-2017-9|work=[[Business Insider]]|accessdate=April 21, 2018|date=September 19, 2017}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 was initially expected to practice with players his age, but only 16 minutes into his first training session, the coaching staff moved him up to the 11-year-old group. Starting in the next session, he primarily practiced with Olimpija's under-14 team, but due to league rules, he only played for the club's under-12 selection team, coming off the bench against opponents three or four years older than him.<ref name=schmitz/><ref name=borntoplay/> Despite his exclusion from under-14 games at the time, Don\u010di\u0107 often asked to attend practice, even when his coach asked him to stay home.<ref name=schmitz/>\n\nRepresenting Olimpija at the under-14 Vasas Intesa Sanpaolo Cup in [[Budapest]] in September 2011, Don\u010di\u0107 was named [[most valuable player]] (MVP) despite finishing as runners-up to [[FC Barcelona B\u00e0squet|FC Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Barcelona wins in Hungary; Doncic MVP|url=http://www.eurohopes.com/news/5575/barcelona_wins_in_hungary;_doncic_mvp|publisher=EuroHopes|accessdate=April 21, 2018|date=September 27, 2011}}</ref> In February 2012, he was [[loan (sports)|loaned]] to Spanish club [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]] for the [[:es:Minicopa Endesa|Minicopa Endesa]], an under-14 Spanish club competition.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Duque|first1=Nacho|title=Luka Doncic, la perla que hace so\u00f1ar al Madrid|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/02/08/baloncesto/acb/1360337892.html|website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|accessdate=April 21, 2018|language=Spanish|date=February 8, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"minicopa\">{{cite web|last1=Alcaraz|first1=Ruben|title=Doncic, new millenium [sic] is close 02/23/2012|url=http://www.eurohopes.com/news/5660/doncic,_new_millenium_is_close|publisher=EuroHopes|accessdate=April 21, 2018|date=February 23, 2012}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107, who was among the youngest players on his team, averaged 13.0 points, 4.0 rebounds, 2.8 assists and 3.3 steals per game to win tournament MVP honours, leading Real Madrid to a second-place finish.<ref name=minicopa/> In April 2012, he took part in the under-13 Lido di Roma Tournament for Olimpija, finishing as MVP and leading scorer with 34.5 points per game. In the semi-final round of the event against Victoria Fermo, he posted 29 points and 15 rebounds, and in a title-clinching win over Lazio, he erupted for 54 points, 11 rebounds, and 10 assists.<ref name=schmitz/><ref name=lido>{{cite web|title=Doncic, now in Rome (54)|url=http://www.eurohopes.com/news/5691/doncic,_now_in_rome_54|publisher=EuroHopes|accessdate=April 21, 2018|date=April 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\n;Real Madrid\n[[File:Luka Doncic, Jorge Parra, Domagoj Proleta y Pablo Poyatos (13919153208) (cropped).jpg|thumb|Don\u010di\u0107 is interviewed after a youth game with [[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid]] in May 2014.]]\nIn September 2012, at 13 years of age, Don\u010di\u0107 signed a five-year contract with Real Madrid, immediately standing out on the under-16 team with coach Paco Redondo.<ref name=borntoplay/><ref name=signs>{{cite web|first1=Nacho| last1 = Duque| url=http://www.marca.com/2013/02/11/baloncesto/nba/noticias/1360576177.html|title=Doncic, el prodigio de 13 a\u00f1os del Madrid|work=Marca|location=Spain|language=Spanish|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> He moved to [[Madrid]], living with football and basketball prospects.<ref name=slam/> In February 2013, Don\u010di\u0107 led Real Madrid to a Minicopa Endesa win, averaging 24.5 points, 13 rebounds, 4 assists, and 6 steals per game. In the final game of the tournament, he contributed 25 points, 16 rebounds, and 5 steals to defeat FC Barcelona and win MVP honours.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Duque |first1=Nacho |title=Doncic, el prodigio de 13 a\u00f1os del Madrid: \"Cuando juego siento lo mismo que cuando sue\u00f1o\" |url=http://www.marca.com/2013/02/11/baloncesto/nba/noticias/1360576177.html |website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |accessdate=June 9, 2018 |date=February 11, 2013}}</ref> In March, Don\u010di\u0107 earned MVP accolades of the under-16 Spain Championship, scoring 25 points in a championship game win over the [[CB Gran Canaria|Gran Canaria]] youth team.<ref name=\"spainchampion\">{{cite web |last1=Novillo |first1=Esteban |title=La estrellas que vienen del baloncesto espa\u00f1ol se presentan al mundo |url=http://www.marca.com/blogs/cuna-de-talentos/2013/03/28/la-estrellas-que-vienen-del-baloncesto.html |website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |accessdate=June 9, 2018 |language=Spanish |date=March 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2014\u201315 season, Don\u010di\u0107 mainly played with Real Madrid's under-18 team and [[Real Madrid Baloncesto B|reserve team]]. With the reserve team, he averaged 13.5 points, 5.9 rebounds, and 3.1 assists, helping them win Group B of the [[2014\u201315 Liga EBA season|Liga EBA]], the [[amateur sports|amateur]] fourth-division of [[Spanish basketball league system|Spanish basketball]].<ref name=eurobasketeba>{{cite web |title=EBA 2014\u201315 Basketball |url=http://www.eurobasket.com/Spain/basketball-League-EBA_2014-2015.asp |publisher=[[Eurobasket.com]] |accessdate=June 3, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Real Madrid II |url=http://basketball.eurobasket.com/team/Spain/Real-Madrid-II/2338?Page=3&Stats=2015 |publisher=[[Eurobasket.com]] |accessdate=June 3, 2018}}</ref> By the end of the season, he earned all-league honourable mention accolades from the basketball website [[Eurobasket.com]].<ref name=eurobasketeba/> In January 2015, Don\u010di\u0107 won the under-18 [[2014\u201315 Euroleague Basketball Next Generation Tournament#Torneig de B\u00e0squet Junior Ciutat de L'Hospitalet|Ciutat de L'Hospitalet Tournament]] and was selected to the All-Tournament Team, despite being two years younger than the rest of the team.<ref name=\"FIBA Article\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.com/news/slovenian-luka-doncic-already-a-big-name-at-just-16|title=Slovenian Luka Doncic already a big name at just 16|date=April 23, 2015|accessdate=July 2, 2018|publisher=FIBA|last=Hein|first=David}}</ref> At the event, on January 6, against the youth team of his former club Union Olimpija, he posted a [[double (basketball)|double-double]] of 13 points, 13 rebounds, 4 assists, and 4 steals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jan 6, 2015: Union Olimpija Junior Team vs. Real Madrid Junior Team |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2015-01-06/Union-Olimpija-Junior-Team-at-Real-Madrid-Junior-Team/205522 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=June 4, 2018}}</ref> In May 2015, he also won the under-18 [[2014\u201315 Euroleague Basketball Next Generation Tournament|Next Generation Tournament]], for which he was selected MVP after helping defeat defending champions [[KK Crvena zvezda (youth)|Crvena zvezda Belgrade]] in the final.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adidasngt.com/u18/news/latest/i/5yliexchngndhh9q/real-madrid-s-young-star-doncic-named-angt-mvp|title=Real Madrid's young star Doncic named ANGT MVP|publisher=AdidasNGT|date=May 17, 2015|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n===Real Madrid===\n====Early years (2015\u201316)====\nOn April 30, 2015, Don\u010di\u0107 made his professional debut for Real Madrid in the [[Liga ACB]] against [[Baloncesto M\u00e1laga|Unicaja]], making his only three-point attempt in under 2 minutes of playing time.<ref name=\"youngestplayer\">{{cite web |title=Doncic, youngest player to make debut for Real Madrid |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2015/04/doncic-youngest-player-to-make-debut-for-real-madrid |publisher=[[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid C.F.]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018 |date=April 30, 2015}}</ref> At 16 years, 2 months, and 2 days of age, he became the youngest player to ever play for Real Madrid in the ACB and the third-youngest debutant in league history, behind only [[Ricky Rubio]] and \u00c1ngel Rebolo.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic, el m\u00e1s joven en debutar con el Real Madrid |url=https://as.com/baloncesto/2015/04/30/acb/1430427303_369647.html |website=[[Diario AS]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018 |language=Spanish |date=May 1, 2015}}</ref> He played 5 games in the [[2014\u201315 ACB season]], averaging 1.6 points and 1.2 rebounds in 4.8 minutes per game.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic Game Logs |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/player/Luka-Doncic/GameLogs/54148/International/2015/4 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2015\u201316 season, Don\u010di\u0107 became a regular member of Real Madrid's senior team. He played against the [[Boston Celtics]] in an NBA preseason game on October 8, 2015, collecting 4 rebounds, 1 assist, and 1 block.<ref name=\"prince\">{{cite web |last1=Pick |first1=David |title=All Hail Luka Doncic, Europe's 16-Year-Old Hoops Prince |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2588799-all-hail-luca-doncic-europes-16-year-old-hoops-prince |website=[[Bleacher Report]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018 |date=November 13, 2015}}</ref> On October 16, at age 16, he debuted in the EuroLeague, scoring 2 points in a loss to [[BC Khimki|Khimki]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=D\u00edaz |first1=Nacho |title=84\u201370: Real Madrid lose to Khimki in Euroleague opener |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2015/10/84-70-real-madrid-lose-to-khimki-in-euroleague-opener |publisher=[[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid C.F.]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018 |date=October 16, 2015}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 became the 21st player ever to debut in the EuroLeague before turning 17.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hein |first1=David |title=Cedevita's U16 hero Musa makes his mark in Euroleague with historic debut |url=http://www.heinnews.com/basketball/nba/cedevitas-u16-hero-musa-makes-his-mark-in-euroleague-with-historic-debut/ |publisher=heinnews |accessdate=October 14, 2018 |date=October 20, 2015}}</ref> On October 18, he recorded 10 points and 4 rebounds in a 94\u201361 win over [[San Sebasti\u00e1n Gipuzkoa BC|Gipuzkoa]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Oct 18, 2015 \u2013 Real Madrid 94, Delteco GBC 61 |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2015-10-18/Real-Madrid-at-Delteco-GBC/223275 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018 |date=October 18, 2015}}</ref> On November 29, Don\u010di\u0107 posted a season-high 15 points, 6 rebounds, and 4 assists against [[Bilbao Basket|Bilbao]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Reyes |first1=Luis Alberto |title=Doncic reclama su sitio (92\u201399) |url=http://www.24segundosenblanco.es/2015/11/doncic-reclama-su-sitio-92-99/ |publisher=24segundosenblanco |accessdate=October 14, 2018 |language=Spanish |date=November 29, 2015}}</ref> With the performance, he set a new ACB record for most points and highest [[Performance Index Rating]] (PIR) in a game for players under age 17.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic's highlights against Valencia |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/acb/322938/luka-doncics-highlights-valencia/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=October 16, 2018 |date=October 7, 2016}}</ref> He scored 12 points and grabbed 5 rebounds on January 7, 2016, against [[PBC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]] in the EuroLeague.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Magnotti |first1=Trevor |title=Luka Doncic is the truth |url=https://fansided.com/2016/12/08/luka-doncic-european-2018-nba-draft/ |publisher=[[FanSided]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018 |date=December 8, 2016}}</ref> After a Real Madrid [[Time-out (sport)|time-out]] in the second quarter of the game, Don\u010di\u0107 made three consecutive three-pointers, recording 9 points in a 2-minute span.<ref>{{cite web |last1=West |first1=Andy |title=Luka Doncic showing enormous potential |url=https://sport360.com/article/other/us-sports/166569/inside-story-real-madrids-basketball-boy-wonder-luka-doncic-showing-enormous-potential |publisher=Sport360 |date=January 3, 2016 |accessdate=October 14, 2018}}</ref> Through 39 games in the [[2015\u201316 ACB season]], he averaged 4.5 points, 2.6 rebounds, and 1.7 assists.<ref name=realgm>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic Player Profile |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/player/Luka-Doncic/Summary/54148 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018}}</ref> In 12 EuroLeague games, he recorded 3.5 points, 2.3 rebounds, and 2 assists per game.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic Game Logs |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/player/Luka-Doncic/GameLogs/54148/International/2016/1 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=October 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n====Rise to prominence (2016\u201317)====\n[[File:Luka Don\u010di\u0107.jpg|thumb|Don\u010di\u0107 shoots a free throw for Real Madrid in January 2017.]]\nDon\u010di\u0107 made his 2016\u201317 season debut on September 30, 2016, against Unicaja, recording 6 points and 4 assists in 19 minutes.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sep 30, 2016 \u2013 Unicaja 90, Real Madrid 101 |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2016-09-30/Unicaja-Malaga-at-Real-Madrid/242351 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=October 16, 2018 |date=September 30, 2016}}</ref> He collected 3 points, 5 rebounds, and 4 assists in an NBA preseason win on October 3, 2016 over the [[Oklahoma City Thunder]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Thunder vs. Real Madrid \u2013 Box Score |url=http://www.espn.com/nba/boxscore?gameId=400897113 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=November 1, 2018 |date=October 3, 2016}}</ref> On December 4, he posted a double-double of 23 points and 11 assists, both season-highs, in a 92\u201376 win over [[Baloncesto Fuenlabrada|Montakit Fuenlabrada]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=D\u00edaz |first1=Nacho |title=92\u201376: Doncic sensational against Montakit Fuenlabrada |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2016/12/92-76-doncic-sensational-against-montakit-fuenlabrada |publisher=[[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid C.F.]] |accessdate=October 16, 2018 |date=December 4, 2016}}</ref> The game earned him his first ACB player of the week honors.<ref name=\"mvpweek\">{{cite web |last1=Stroggylakis |first1=Antonis |title=Luka Doncic is MVP of the Week in Spain |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/acb/430794/luka-doncic-mvp-week-spain/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=October 16, 2018 |date=April 9, 2017}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 scored a team-high 17 points in a EuroLeague victory over [[BC \u017dalgiris|\u017dalgiris Kaunas]] on December 8, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic da la victoria al Real Madrid en el \u00faltimo minuto |url=http://www.rtve.es/deportes/20161208/doncic-da-victoria-real-madrid-ultimo-minuto/1451707.shtml |publisher=[[RTVE]] |accessdate=October 16, 2018 |language=Spanish |date=December 8, 2016}}</ref> After recording 16 points, 6 rebounds, 5 assists, and 3 steals in a 95\u201372 win over [[Brose Bamberg]] on December 22, he was named [[EuroLeague MVP of the Round|MVP of the Round]] in the EuroLeague, becoming the youngest player to ever do so.<ref>{{cite web |title=Round 13 Co-MVPs: Luka Doncic and Mike James |url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/7hnibo6ccfhnk7k9/round-13-co-mvps-luka-doncic-and-mike-james |publisher=[[EuroLeague]] |accessdate=October 17, 2018 |date=December 22, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"unanimous\">{{cite web |title=Rising Star Trophy: Madrid's Doncic is unanimous winner |url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/7ssonijxmjl9vexx |publisher=[[EuroLeague]] |accessdate=October 18, 2018 |date=May 10, 2017}}</ref> He earned the same honor on January 14, 2017, after posting 10 points, 11 rebounds, and 8 assists to help beat [[Maccabi Tel Aviv B.C.|Maccabi Tel Aviv]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Regular Season Round 17 MVP: Luka Doncic, Real Madrid |url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/7ji5ruia83h9ucp3/regular-season-round-17-mvp-luka-doncic-real-madrid |publisher=[[EuroLeague]] |accessdate=October 17, 2018 |date=January 14, 2017}}</ref> On February 9, Don\u010di\u0107 recorded 5 points, 7 rebounds, and 11 assists to defeat [[BC UNICS|UNICS Kazan]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Maestro Doncic, road victory for Real Madrid over Unics Kazan |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/euroleague/398283/maestro-doncic-road-victory-real-madrid-unics-kazan/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=October 18, 2018 |date=February 9, 2017}}</ref> He scored a season-high 23 points on February 18, in the [[2017 Copa del Rey de Baloncesto|Spanish King's Cup]] versus [[Saski Baskonia|Baskonia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Baskonia 99, Real Madrid 103 |url=http://www.acb.com/fichas/CREY81005.php |publisher=[[Liga ACB]] |accessdate=October 17, 2018 |language=Spanish |date=February 18, 2017}}</ref> After scoring 13 points and grabbing 8 rebounds in the [[2017 EuroLeague Playoffs]] against [[Dar\u00fc\u015f\u015fafaka S.K.|Dar\u00fc\u015f\u015fafaka]] on April 26, he shared MVP of the Round accolades with two other players.<ref>{{cite web |title=Playoffs Game 3 tri-MVPs: Dunston, Ayon and Doncic |url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/7rrdm98plh6lm8bt |publisher=[[EuroLeague]] |accessdate=October 18, 2018 |date=April 27, 2017}}</ref> Two days later, he won the award outright, posting 11 points, 5 rebounds, and 7 assists to lead Real Madrid to a [[2017 EuroLeague Final Four|EuroLeague Final Four]] berth.<ref>{{cite web |title=Playoffs Game 4 MVP: Luka Doncic, Real Madrid |url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/7rwjsoenryho3niw |publisher=[[EuroLeague]] |accessdate=October 18, 2018 |date=April 29, 2017}}</ref> Through 42 ACB games in the season, Don\u010di\u0107 averaged 7.5 points, 4.4 rebounds, and 3 assists, and through 35 EuroLeague contests, he averaged 7.8 points, 4.5 rebounds, and 4.2 assists per game.<ref name=realgm/> He was named [[EuroLeague Rising Star]] by unanimous vote and also claimed the [[ACB Best Young Player Award]].<ref name=unanimous/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Blum |first1=Matt |title=Meet Luka Doncic: The Next Great European Prospect |url=http://thesportsquotient.com/nba/2017/9/21/meet-luka-doncic-the-next-great-european-prospect |publisher=The Sports Quotient |accessdate=October 18, 2018 |date=September 21, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019041023/http://thesportsquotient.com/nba/2017/9/21/meet-luka-doncic-the-next-great-european-prospect |archive-date=October 19, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n====MVP season (2017\u201318)====\nDon\u010di\u0107 assumed a greater role for Real Madrid entering the 2017\u201318 season, after the team's star player [[Sergio Llull]] suffered a [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|torn ACL]] during [[EuroBasket 2017]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kalbrosky |first1=Bryan |title=Top NBA prospect Luka Doncic to see bigger role after Rockets' draftee Sergio Llull is injured |url=https://hoopshype.com/2017/08/10/top-nba-prospect-luka-doncic-to-see-bigger-role-after-rockets-draftee-sergio-llull-is-injured/ |publisher=HoopsHype |accessdate=October 19, 2018 |date=August 10, 2017}}</ref> In his season debut on October 1, 2017, he recorded 8 points, 6 rebounds, and 4 assists in a 94\u201388 victory over [[BC Andorra|MoraBanc Andorra]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Oct 1, 2017 \u2013 MoraBanc Andorra 88, Real Madrid 94 |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2017-10-01/MoraBanc-Andorra-at-Real-Madrid/273185 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=October 19, 2018 |date=October 1, 2017}}</ref> In his first EuroLeague game of the season, on October 12, Don\u010di\u0107 scored a career-high 27 points to help defeat [[Anadolu Efes S.K.|Anadolu Efes]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic nets his highest points total with Real Madrid |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2017/10/doncic-nets-his-highest-points-total-with-real-madrid |publisher=[[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid C.F.]] |accessdate=October 19, 2018 |date=October 12, 2017}}</ref> In his next game, he nearly recorded a triple-double against [[Valencia Basket|Valencia]], with 16 points, 10 assists, and 7 rebounds.<ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic's near triple-double performance vs Valencia |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/acb/534210/doncics-near-triple-double-performance-vs-valencia/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=October 19, 2018 |date=October 16, 2017}}</ref> On October 24, Don\u010di\u0107 was named EuroLeague MVP of the Round after erupting for 27 points, 8 rebounds, 5 assists, and 3 steals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Round 3 MVP: Luka Doncic, Real Madrid |url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/8aga66tcihey9cqq/round-3-mvp-luka-doncic-real-madrid |publisher=[[EuroLeague]] |accessdate=October 19, 2018 |date=October 26, 2017}}</ref> He was named MVP of the Round again two days later, eclipsing his career-best with 28 points in an 87\u201366 win over \u017dalgiris Kaunas. Don\u010di\u0107 also grabbed 9 rebounds and had 4 assists in the game.<ref>{{cite web |title=Round 4 MVP: Luka Doncic, Real Madrid |url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/8al85pqyvecsiwi3 |publisher=[[EuroLeague]] |accessdate=October 19, 2018 |date=October 28, 2017}}</ref> At the end of October, he earned [[EuroLeague MVP of the Month]] honors, becoming the youngest player to ever win the award.<ref>{{cite web |title=Turkish Airlines EuroLeague MVP for October: Luka Doncic, Real Madrid |url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/8aqi43ypxb5l69kn/turkish-airlines-euroleague-mvp-for-october-luka-doncic-real-madrid |publisher=[[EuroLeague]] |accessdate=October 19, 2018 |date=October 30, 2017}}</ref> On December 8, he set a career-high in scoring, with 33 points, 6 rebounds, and 4 assists against [[Olympiacos B.C.|Olympiacos Piraeus]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Stroggilakis |first1=Antonis |title=Doncic: \"\u0399 don\u2019t care for my career high because we lost\" |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/euroleague/570196/doncic-dont-care-career-high-lost/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=October 19, 2018 |date=December 8, 2017}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 led Real Madrid to a 79\u201377 victory over defending EuroLeague champion [[Fenerbah\u00e7e Basketball|Fenerbah\u00e7e Do\u011fu\u015f]] on December 28, contributing 20 points, 10 assists, and 8 rebounds.<ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic flirts with triple-double, Real beats the champs |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/euroleague/583905/doncic-flirts-triple-double-real-beats-champs/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=December 28, 2017}}</ref> Following a 24-point outburst in 22 minutes versus [[CB Estudiantes|Movistar Estudiantes]] on December 31, he was selected as Player of the Round in the ACB.<ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic, player of round 14 in the Endesa League |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2017/12/doncic-player-of-round-14-in-the-endesa-league |publisher=[[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid C.F.]] |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=December 31, 2017}}</ref> He was later named ACB Player of the Month for December, becoming the award's youngest recipient ever.<ref>{{cite news|title=Luka Doncic, MVP Movistar de Diciembre|url=http://www.acb.com/redaccion.php?id=137417|accessdate=January 1, 2018|work=acb.com|date=January 1, 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n{{multiple image\n<!-- Essential parameters -->\n| align = right\n| direction = horizontal\n| width = 160\n| image1 = Luka Don\u010di\u0107 7 Real Madrid Baloncesto Euroleague 20171012 (2).jpg\n| width1 = \n| alt1 = \n| caption1 =\n| image3 = Josh Adams 14 Anadolu Efes Euroleague 20171012 (2).jpg\n| width3 =\n| alt3 = \n| caption3 =\n| header = Don\u010di\u0107 versus [[Anadolu Efes S.K.|Anadolu Efes]] in 2017\n| header_align = <!-- left/right/center -->\n| header_background = \n| footer = (left) with Real Madrid; (right) guarded by [[Josh Adams (basketball)|Josh Adams]]\n| footer_align = <!-- left/right/center -->\n| footer_background = \n| background color = \n}}\nOn February 9, 2018, Don\u010di\u0107 led his team with 27 points in a losing effort to Olympiacos, 80\u201379.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bueno |first1=Edu |title=79\u201380: Madrid had the last play to down Olympiacos |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/02/79-80-madrid-had-the-last-play-to-down-olympiacos |publisher=[[Real Madrid Baloncesto|Real Madrid C.F.]] |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=February 9, 2018}}</ref> He had another strong performance on February 17, versus [[CB 1939 Canarias|Iberostar Tenerife]] in the [[2018 Copa del Rey de Baloncesto|2018 Spanish King's Cup]], posting 17 points, 7 rebounds, 5 assists, and 4 steals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Feb 17, 2018 \u2013 Real Madrid 77, Iberostar Tenerife 59 |url=https://basketball.realgm.com/international/boxscore/2018-02-17/Real-Madrid-at-Iberostar-Tenerife/298045 |publisher=[[RealGM]] |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=February 17, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Garc\u00eda |first1=Dioni |title=Doncic conduce al Madrid a la final de Copa |url=https://www.laopiniondemurcia.es/deportes/2018/02/17/iberostar-tenerife-real-madrid-directo/898962.html |website=La Opini\u00f3n de Murcia |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |language=Spanish |date=February 17, 2018}}</ref> On March 30, 2018, Don\u010di\u0107 scored 24 points, grabbed 9 rebounds, and made a game-winning three-pointer with under a second left in regulation to beat Crvena zvezda Belgrade, 82\u201379.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gartland |first1=Dan |title=Potential No. 1 Draft Pick Luka Doncic Hits Ankle-Breaking Step-Back Buzzer-Beater |url=https://www.si.com/nba/2018/03/30/luka-doncic-real-madrid-nba-draft-prospect-buzzer-beater-video |website=[[Sports Illustrated]] |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=March 30, 2018}}</ref> On May 9, he recorded 17 points, 10 rebounds, and 10 assists in 22 minutes against [[CB Sevilla|Real Betis Energ\u00eda Plus]], for the first triple-double in the ACB since the [[2006\u201307 ACB season|2006\u201307 season]] and the seventh in league history.<ref name=\"tripledouble\">{{cite web |last1=Stroggylakis |first1=Antonis |title=Luka Doncic notches first career triple-double |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/acb/672135/luka-doncic-notches-first-career-triple-double/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=October 22, 2018 |date=May 9, 2018}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 finished with 16 points, 7 rebounds, and 2 assists on May 18, in a 92\u201383 win over CSKA Moscow in the EuroLeague semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/nba/2018/5/18/17369976/luka-doncic-stats-euroleague-final-four-pick-draft|title=Luka Doncic looks like a No. 1 pick in EuroLeague semi-final win|last=Ellentuck|first=Matt|publisher=SB Nation|date=May 18, 2018|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> On May 20, he guided Real Madrid to a [[2018 EuroLeague Final Four|EuroLeague finals]] victory over Fenerbah\u00e7e Do\u011fu\u015f.<ref name=\"EuroLeague18Champ\">{{cite news|title=Real Madrid is 2018 EuroLeague champion|url=http://www.euroleague.net/main/results/showgame?gamecode=260&seasoncode=E2017#!report|accessdate=May 20, 2018|work=euroleague.net|date=May 20, 2018}}</ref> He was subsequently named [[EuroLeague Final Four MVP]] after scoring 15 points.<ref name=\"EuroLeagueMVPF4\">{{cite news|title=Doncic chosen Final Four MVP|url=http://www.euroleague.net/final-four/belgrade-2018/news/i/8r3oqram9e8uuqvt/doncic-chosen-final-four-mvp|accessdate=May 20, 2018|work=euroleague.net|date=May 20, 2018}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 won the [[EuroLeague MVP]] award, being its youngest winner, after averaging 16 points, 4.9 rebounds, and 4.3 assists per game over 33 EuroLeague games and leading the league in PIR.<ref name=\"EuroLeague2018MVP\">{{cite news|title=2017\u201318 Turkish Airlines EuroLeague MVP: Luka Doncic, Real Madrid|url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/8qwovagussoccaq6|work=[[EuroLeague]]|date=May 19, 2018|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> He also repeated as the EuroLeague Rising Star, becoming the third back-to-back winner of the award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euroleague.net/news/i/8q3k4gyd7iac7dnc/2017-18-turkish-airlines-euroleague-rising-star-luka-doncic-real-madrid|title=2017\u201318 Turkish Airlines EuroLeague Rising Star: Luka Doncic, Real Madrid C.F.|work=Euroleague.net|accessdate= May 8, 2018}}</ref> In addition, Don\u010di\u0107 earned the ACB Best Young Player and [[ACB Most Valuable Player Award|MVP]] accolades, after helping his team defeat Kirolbet Baskonia in the [[2018 ACB Playoffs#Finals|league finals]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Luka Doncic, MVP Movistar de la Liga Endesa 2017\u201318|url=http://www.acb.com/redaccion.php?id=140829|accessdate=May 26, 2018|work=ACB.com|date=May 24, 2018|language=Spanish}}</ref> On June 29, 2018, he parted ways with Real Madrid.<ref>{{cite news |title=Doncic: the kid who became a star at Real Madrid |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/06/doncic-the-kid-who-became-a-star-at-real-madrid |work=Real Madrid C.F. \u2013 Web Oficial |date=June 29, 2018|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Luka Doncic's farewell letter: two dreams  |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/06/luka-doncics-farewell-letter-two-dreams |accessdate=June 30, 2018 |work=Real Madrid C.F. \u2013 Web Oficial |date=June 29, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== EuroLeague 2010\u201320 All-Decade Team ====\nIn November 2019, Don\u010di\u0107 was nominated to the [[EuroLeague Basketball 2010\u201320 All-Decade Team|EuroLeague 2010\u201320 All-Decade Team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=All-Decade Nominee: Luka Doncic |url=https://www.euroleague.net/news/i/a7nfxe77oaifqhse/all-decade-nominee-luka-doncic |website=euroleague.net |accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref> On March 2020, he was selected to the 2010\u201320 All-Decade Team.<ref>{{cite web |title=2010-20 All-Decade Team: Luka Doncic |url=https://www.euroleague.net/news/i/aha8l4exn7k7tka6/2010-20-all-decade-team-luka-doncic |website=euroleague.net |accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=NBA star Don\u010di\u0107 makes it into EuroLeague all-decade team |url=http://www.sloveniatimes.com/nba-star-doncic-makes-it-into-euroleague-all-decade-team |website=sloveniatimes.com |accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Dallas Mavericks===\n====Rookie season (2018\u201319)====\nOn June 21, 2018, Don\u010di\u0107 was selected with the third overall pick by the [[Atlanta Hawks]] in the [[2018 NBA draft]]. He was then traded to the [[Dallas Mavericks]] in exchange for the draft rights to [[Trae Young]] and a protected future first round pick in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/23867178/2018-nba-draft-dallas-mavericks-acquire-luke-doncic-send-draft-rights-trae-young-atlanta-hawks|title=Luka Doncic headed to Mavs, Trae Young to Hawks after teams swap picks|date= June 21, 2018|access-date=June 21, 2018|publisher=ESPN|last=MacMahon|first=Tim}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mavs.com/mavericks-acquire-draft-rights-to-third-overall-pick-luka-doncic/|title=Mavericks acquire draft rights to third-overall pick Luka Doncic|date=June 21, 2018|access-date=June 21, 2018|publisher=[[Dallas Mavericks]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708143351/https://www.mavs.com/mavericks-acquire-draft-rights-to-third-overall-pick-luka-doncic/|archive-date=July 8, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> After the draft, Mavericks head coach [[Rick Carlisle]] said, \"At one point, we thought there might be a slight chance Don\u010di\u0107 could fall to us, but a couple of days ago it was pretty clear that there was no way that was going to happen. He's just too good. We get a guy we think is franchise foundation piece.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zillgitt |first1=Jeff |title=Mavericks believe European sensation Luka Doncic can be a cornerstone like Dirk Nowitzki |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nba/2018/06/22/mavericks-luka-doncic-dirk-nowitzki-cornerstone/726564002/ |website=[[USA Today]] |accessdate=June 25, 2018 |date=June 22, 2018}}</ref> He signed his rookie contract with the Mavericks on July 9, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mavericks sign third overall pick Luka Doncic|url=https://www.mavs.com/mavericks-sign-third-overall-pick-luka-doncic/|publisher=National Basketball Association|date=July 9, 2018|accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 did not play at the [[2018 NBA Summer League]] due to his late buyout from Real Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Price |first1=David |title=Mavs did the right thing in not allowing Luka Doncic to play summer league ball |url=https://www.mavs.com/mavs-did-the-right-thing-in-not-allowing-luka-doncic-to-play-summer-league-ball/ |publisher=National Basketball Association |accessdate=September 30, 2018 |date=July 12, 2018}}</ref> Before the [[2018\u201319 NBA season|2018\u201319 season]], [[ESPN]] considered him to be the favorite to win the [[NBA Rookie of the Year Award]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Summer Forecast: 2018\u201319 NBA Rookie of the Year |url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/24245975/nba-rookie-year-predictions-espn-summer-forecast |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=September 30, 2018 |date=August 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\nDon\u010di\u0107 made his regular season debut on October 17, 2018, recording 10 points, 8 rebounds and 4 assists, in a 121\u2013100 loss to the [[Phoenix Suns]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nba/boxscore?gameId=401070216|title=Booker's late onslaught lifts Suns past Mavs 121\u2013100|publisher=National Basketball Association|date=October 17, 2018|accessdate=October 17, 2018}}</ref> On October 20, Don\u010di\u0107 recorded 26 points and 6 rebounds in a 140\u2013136 win over the [[Minnesota Timberwolves]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=MacMahon |first1=Tim |title=Dennis Smith and Luka Doncic show Dallas a sign of the future |url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/25039525/dennis-smith-jr-luka-doncic-show-dallas-mavericks-sign-future-minnesota-timberwolves-nba |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=October 21, 2018}}</ref> He became the youngest 20-point scorer in franchise history.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Karalla |first1=Bobby |title=The Fast Break: Mavs vs. Wolves |url=https://www.mavs.com/the-fast-break-mavs-vs-wolves/ |publisher=[[Dallas Mavericks]] |accessdate=October 21, 2018 |date=October 21, 2018}}</ref> On October 29, Don\u010di\u0107 posted 31 points and 8 rebounds in a 113\u2013108 loss to the [[San Antonio Spurs]], for his first 30-point game in the NBA.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mavericks' Luka Doncic: Explodes for 31 points in OT loss |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/basketball/news/mavericks-luka-doncic-explodes-for-31-points-in-ot-loss/ |publisher=[[CBS Sports]] |accessdate=October 30, 2018 |date=October 30, 2018}}</ref> He recorded his first NBA double-double on November 19, with 15 points and 10 rebounds in a 98\u201388 loss to the [[Memphis Grizzlies]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Mavericks' Luka Doncic: Has double-double in loss |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/basketball/news/mavericks-luka-doncic-has-double-double-in-loss/ |publisher=[[CBS Sports]] |accessdate=December 3, 2018 |date=November 19, 2018}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 was named [[NBA Rookie of the Month Award|NBA Rookie of the Month]] in the [[Western Conference (NBA)|Western Conference]] for November 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mavs' Luka Doncic named Western Conference Rookie of the Month |url=https://sportsday.dallasnews.com/dallas-mavericks/mavericks/2018/12/03/mavs-luka-doncic-named-western-conference-rookie-month |website=[[The Dallas Morning News]] |accessdate=December 3, 2018 |date=December 3, 2018}}</ref> On December 8, Don\u010di\u0107 scored 21 points in a 107\u2013104 win over the [[Houston Rockets]]. After initial struggles, he produced a personal 11\u20130 run in the final minutes of the game.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nathan |first1=Alec |title=Luka Doncic Goes on Dazzling 11\u20130 Run by Himself, Drops 21 in Win vs. Rockets |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2809913-luka-doncic-goes-on-dazzling-11-0-run-by-himself-drops-21-in-win-vs-rockets |website=[[Bleacher Report]] |accessdate=December 9, 2018 |date=December 9, 2018}}</ref> On December 28, Don\u010di\u0107 scored 34 points and became the youngest NBA player to make 7 three-pointers in a game.<ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic drops 34 in loss to Pelicans |url=http://www.espn.com/video/clip?id=25635853&ex_cid=espnapi_public |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=January 1, 2019 |date=December 28, 2018}}</ref> He was named Western Conference Rookie of the Month for December 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Doncic wins monthly honor, and would be an All-Star starter if the voting ended today|url=https://www.mavs.com/doncic-named-western-conference-rookie-of-the-month-for-the-second-month-in-a-row/|website=Mavs.com|accessdate=January 3, 2019|date=January 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190104175558/https://www.mavs.com/doncic-named-western-conference-rookie-of-the-month-for-the-second-month-in-a-row/|archive-date=January 4, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> On January 21, Don\u010di\u0107 recorded his first NBA triple-double with 18 points, 11 rebounds and 10 assists in a 116\u2013106 loss to the [[Milwaukee Bucks]], which made him the second-youngest player in NBA history to accomplish the feat at 19 years and 327 days old, behind only [[Markelle Fultz]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Mavericks' Luka Doncic: Posts first career triple-double |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/basketball/news/mavericks-luka-doncic-posts-first-career-triple-double/ |website=cbssports.com |accessdate=January 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mavericks' Luka Doncic Becomes 2nd-Youngest NBA Player to Record Triple-Double |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2816923-mavericks-luka-doncic-becomes-2nd-youngest-nba-player-to-record-triple-double |website=bleacherreport.com |accessdate=January 28, 2019}}</ref> On January 27, Don\u010di\u0107 scored a season-high 35 points and recorded his second NBA triple-double adding 12 rebounds and 10 assists in a 123\u2013120 loss to the [[Toronto Raptors]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic Becomes First Teenager in NBA History to Record 30-Point Triple Double |url=https://www.si.com/nba/2019/01/27/Luka-Doncic-first-teen-30-point-triple-double-raptors-mavericks |website=Sports Illustrated |accessdate=January 28, 2019}}</ref> He became the first teenager in NBA history with a 30-point triple-double and with multiple triple-doubles.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic scores 35, is first teen with 30-point triple-double |url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/25866566/luka-doncic-scores-35-first-teen-30-point-triple-double |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=January 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic becomes first NBA player with multiple triple-doubles as teenager |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/doncic-becomes-first-nba-player-042815711.html?guccounter=1 |publisher=Yahoo! |accessdate=January 28, 2019}}</ref> Two days later, Don\u010di\u0107 was named a confirmed participant for the World Team in the [[2019 NBA All-Star Game|2019]] [[Rising Stars Challenge]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Doncic, Simmons headline Mtn Dew Ice Rising Stars rosters |url=https://www.nba.com/article/2019/01/29/2019-mtn-dew-ice-rising-stars-roster-official-release |publisher=National Basketball Association |accessdate=January 30, 2019}}</ref> Despite being second in fan voting, behind only [[LeBron James]], and ranked 8th in total voting score, Don\u010di\u0107 wasn't selected for the Western Conference All-Stars in the [[2019 NBA All-Star Game]].<ref>{{cite web |title=NBA All-Star Game 2019: LeBron, Giannis, Luka Doncic Lead 3rd Voting Results |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2816254-nba-all-star-game-2019-lebron-giannis-luka-doncic-lead-3rd-voting-results |website=bleacherreport.com |accessdate=February 1, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mavs rookie Luka Doncic not named an NBA All-Star starter |url=https://247sports.com/nba/mavericks/Article/Despite-being-2nd-in-West-fan-voting-Mavs-Luka-Doncic-misses-being-an-All-Star-starter-by-narrow-margin-128260735/ |website=247sports.com |accessdate=February 1, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=@JoshEberley on Western Conference Voting Results |url=https://twitter.com/JoshEberley/status/1088592344952201216/photo/1 |publisher=Twitter |accessdate=February 1, 2019}}{{Primary source inline|date=April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic fails to make the 2019 All-Star game |url=https://www.mavsmoneyball.com/2019/1/31/18206145/luka-doncic-not-voted-to-all-star-game |website=mavsmoneyball.com |accessdate=February 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 6, Don\u010di\u0107 recorded his third triple-double with 19 points, 10 rebounds and 11 assists in a 99\u201393 win over the [[Charlotte Hornets]], which made him the youngest player in NBA history to record three triple-doubles.<ref>{{cite web |title=NBA: Doncic nets triple-double in Mavs' win over Hornets |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/sports/02/07/19/nba-doncic-nets-triple-double-in-mavs-win-over-hornets |website=news.abs-cbn.com |accessdate=February 8, 2019}}</ref> He edges [[Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame|Hall of Famer]] [[Magic Johnson]] by 117 days.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic picks up third triple-double in his last seven games |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/luka-doncic-picks-third-triple-double-last-seven-games-060955785.html?guccounter=1 |publisher=Yahoo! |accessdate=February 8, 2019}}</ref> On February 25, Don\u010di\u0107 recorded his fourth triple-double with 28 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists in a 121\u2013112 loss to the [[Los Angeles Clippers]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic has his 4th triple-double in loss to Clippers |url=https://www.foxsports.com/southwest/story/luka-doncic-has-his-4th-triple-double-in-loss-to-clippers-022619 |publisher=Fox Sports |accessdate=March 3, 2019}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 has four of the five triple-doubles recorded by teenagers in NBA history.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic has 4 of the 5 triple-doubles recorded by teenagers in NBA history |url=https://clutchpoints.com/mavs-news-luka-doncic-has-4-of-the-5-triple-doubles-recorded-by-teenagers-in-nba-history/ |website=clutchpoints.com |accessdate=March 3, 2019}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 was named Western Conference Rookie of the Month for January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Luka Doncic wins his fourth straight Rookie of the Month award|url=https://www.mavs.com/luka-doncic-wins-his-fourth-straight-rookie-of-the-month-award/|website=Mavs.com|accessdate=March 1, 2019}}</ref> His eight triple-doubles ranked fourth on the season behind [[Russell Westbrook]] (34), [[Nikola Joki\u0107]] (12) and [[Ben Simmons]] (10), as well as tied with LeBron James.<ref>{{cite web |title=Stats: Players General Traditional |url=https://stats.nba.com/players/traditional/?sort=TD3&dir=-1&Season=2018-19&SeasonType=Regular%20Season |publisher=National Basketball Association |accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 became just the fifth player in NBA history to average at least 20 points, 5 rebounds and 5 assists in his rookie year, joining [[Oscar Robertson]] ([[1960\u201361 NBA season|1960\u201361]]), [[Michael Jordan]] ([[1984\u201385 NBA season|1984\u201385]]), LeBron James ([[2003\u201304 NBA season|2003\u201304]]), and [[Tyreke Evans]] ([[2009\u201310 NBA season|2009\u201310]]).<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic: A Rookie Year in Context|url=https://hashtagbasketball.com/dallas-mavericks/content/luka-doncic-rookie-year-context|website=Hashtag Basketball|accessdate=May 15, 2019}}</ref> In May, Don\u010di\u0107 was selected unanimously to the [[NBA All-Rookie Team|All-Rookie First Team]], and in June he received the [[NBA Rookie of the Year Award]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Young, Doncic lead 2018\u201319 All-Rookie First Team |url=https://www.nba.com/2018-19-all-rookie-teams-official-release |publisher=National Basketball Association |accessdate=May 27, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic Wins 2019 NBA Rookie of the Year over Trae Young, DeAndre Ayton |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2832020-luka-doncic-wins-2019-nba-rookie-of-the-year-over-trae-young-deandre-ayton |website=bleacherreport.com}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 became the second European player, after [[Pau Gasol]], who won the award and the sixth overall winner not born in the United States.\n\n====First All-Star selection (2019\u201320)====\nDon\u010di\u0107 made his first triple-double of the season on October 25, 2019, posting 25 points, 10 rebounds, and 10 assists to help the Mavericks defeat the [[New Orleans Pelicans]], 123\u2013116.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dallas Mavericks: Luka Doncic has ninth triple-double in win over Pelicans |url=https://thesmokingcuban.com/2019/10/26/dallas-mavericks-2019-luka-doncic-game-2-pelicans/ |website=thesmokingcuban.com |accessdate=October 28, 2019}}</ref> In two consecutive games, on November 1-3, he not only recorded two triple-doubles but matched a career-high 15 assists in both games.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic posts record 31/15/13 triple-double vs. Lakers |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/nba-news/960054/luka-doncic-posts-record-31-15-13-triple-double-vs-lakers/ |website=eurohoops.net |accessdate=November 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Six stats to know from Luka Doncic's historic triple-double against the Cleveland Cavaliers |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/au/nba/news/six-stats-to-know-from-luka-doncics-historic-triple-double-against-the-cleveland-cavaliers/5xm41suon1x91nfxcx1ny2y91 |website=sportingnews.com |accessdate=November 15, 2019}}</ref> On November 8, Don\u010di\u0107 scored a career-high 38 points and recorded his twelfth NBA triple-double by adding 14 rebounds and 10 assists during a 106\u2013102 loss to the [[New York Knicks]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic thrives with triple-double and career high |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/nba-news/963970/luka-doncic-thrives-with-triple-double-and-career-high/ |website=eurohoops.net |accessdate=November 15, 2019}}</ref> Ten days later, in a 117\u2013110 win over the [[San Antonio Spurs]], Don\u010di\u0107 recorded a career-high 42 points and his sixth triple-double of the season by adding 11 rebounds and 12 assists.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic becomes 2nd youngest to post 40-point triple-double |url=https://www.nba.com/article/2019/11/18/luka-doncic-2nd-youngest-post-40-point-triple-double |website=nba.com |accessdate=19 November 2019}}</ref> He made NBA history in a 142\u201394 win over the [[Golden State Warriors]] on November 20 when he posted 35 points, 10 rebounds, and 11 assists; thus becoming the youngest player to have 35-point triple-doubles in succession, breaking [[Oscar Robertson]]'s record, and only the fourth player to record it since the 1983\u201384 season, joining [[Michael Jordan]], [[James Harden]], and [[Russell Westbrook]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic dominates for yet another monster triple-double |url=https://www.nba.com/article/2019/11/20/luka-doncic-dominates-warriors-latest-monster-triple-double |website=nba.com |accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mavericks' Luka Doncic posts 35-point triple-double in 25 minutes |url=https://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/28126914/mavericks-luka-doncic-posts-35-point-triple-double-25-minutes |website=espn.com |accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref> In November, Don\u010di\u0107 was named the NBA Western Conference [[2019\u201320 NBA season#Players of the Week|Player of the Week]] for Week 5 (November 18\u201324); which was his first NBA Player of the Week award.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic, Spencer Dinwiddie named NBA Players of the Week |url=https://www.nba.com/article/2019/11/25/nba-players-week-5-spencer-dinwiddie-luka-doncic |website=nba.com |accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic earns first career Player of the Week award |url=https://www.mavs.com/luka-doncic-earns-first-career-player-of-the-week-award/ |website=mavs.com |accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref> On 3 December, he won his first NBA Player of the Month award when he was named the NBA Western Conference [[2019\u201320 NBA season#Players of the Month|Player of the Month]] for October and November; becoming the youngest Western Conference Player of the Month winner since the league began issuing the award by conference in the 2001\u201302 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Doncic Named Western Conference Player of the Month |url=https://www.foxsports.com/southwest/story/luka-doncic-named-western-conference-player-of-the-month-120319 |publisher=Fox Sports |accessdate=3 December 2019 |date=3 December 2019}}</ref> In December, he was also named ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' 2019 Breakout of the Year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mavericks' Luka Doncic Wins Sports Illustrated's Breakout of the Year Award |url=https://www.si.com/sportsperson/2019/12/04/luka-doncic-dallas-mavericks-sports-illustrated-breakout-award |work=[[Sports Illustrated]] |accessdate=4 December 2019}}</ref> On December 8, 2019, Don\u010di\u0107 surpassed the record for the most consecutive games with at least 20 points, 5 rebounds, and 5 assists since the ABA-NBA merger in 1976. Michael Jordan previously held the record with 18 consecutive games in 1989.<ref>{{cite web |title= Luka Doncic passes Michael Jordan with 19th straight game of 20-5-5 |url=https://www.nba.com/article/2019/12/08/doncic-passes-jordan-20-5-5 |website=nba.com |accessdate=December 11, 2019 }}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 made his tenth season triple-double on January 4, 2020, posting 39 points, 12 rebounds, and 10 assists in a 123\u2013120 loss to the [[Charlotte Hornets]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Watch Luka Doncic\u2019s NBA-leading 10th triple-double, but Mavs still fall to Hornets in OT |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/watch-luka-doncic-nba-leading-151335381.html|website=yahoo.com |accessdate=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nDuring the [[2019\u201320 NBA season|2019\u201320 season]], Don\u010di\u0107 was selected to his first [[2020 NBA All-Star Game|NBA All-Star Game]] as a Western Conference starter.<ref>{{cite web |first=Sekou |last=Smith |title=Captains LeBron James, Giannis Antetokounmpo headline starters for NBA All-Star 2020 |url=https://www.nba.com/article/2020/01/23/2020-all-star-starters-and-captains-announced |website=NBA.com |date=23 January 2020}}</ref> He became the youngest European player to start in an All-Star game.<ref>{{cite web |title=Luka Don\u010di\u0107 named starter for 2020 NBA All-star game |url=https://www.mavs.com/luka-all-star-2020-press-release/ |publisher=mavs.com |accessdate=14 February 2020}}</ref> On 4 March, Don\u010di\u0107 recorded his 22nd career triple-double, passing Jason Kidd for the most in franchise history, as he registered 30 points, 17 rebounds and 10 assists in a 127\u2013123 overtime victory over the [[New Orleans Pelicans]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Second-year Luka Doncic sets Mavericks\u2019 career triple-double record (video)|url=https://nba.nbcsports.com/2020/03/05/second-year-luka-doncic-sets-mavericks-career-triple-double-record-video/|publisher=mavs.com |accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==National team career==\n===Junior national team===\n[[File:EuroBasket 2017 Finland vs Slovenia 29.jpg|thumb|Don\u010di\u0107 (front) during [[EuroBasket 2017]]]]\nDon\u010di\u0107 was set to play at the Division B tournament of the [[2014 FIBA Europe Under-16 Championship]] but was forced to withdraw from the tournament with a knee injury. In December 2014, he took part in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] tournament in [[Sz\u00e9kesfeh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]], Hungary, averaging 35.3 points and 7.6 rebounds per game, while shooting 81 percent on two-pointers and 57 percent on [[three-point field goal|three-pointers]].<ref name=\"FIBA Article\" />\n\n===Senior national team===\nOn September 22, 2016, Don\u010di\u0107 announced that he would represent the senior men's [[Slovenia national basketball team|Slovenian national team]] for the rest of his career.<ref>{{cite web|title=LUKA DON\u010cI\u0106: \"Hvala \u0160paniji, Slovenija je moja izbira!\"|url=http://www.kosarka.si/luka-doncic-hvala-spaniji-slovenija-je-moja-izbira/|website=kosarka.si|accessdate=September 22, 2016|language=sl-SL|date=September 22, 2016}}</ref> He had previously been linked with a number of other national teams, including [[Serbia men's national basketball team|Serbia]] and [[Spain men's national basketball team|Spain]].<ref name=\"rtv-intervju\">{{cite news | url= http://www.rtvslo.si/sport/kosarka/doncic-na-evropskem-prvenstvu-gremo-po-medaljo/413818 | title = Don\u010di\u0107: Na evropskem prvenstvu gremo po medaljo |trans-title=Doncic: At the Eurobasket we are aiming for a medal  | publisher = [[RTV Slovenija]] | date = January 30, 2017 | accessdate = February 2, 2017 | language = Slovenian }}</ref> His national team [[roommate]] became [[Goran Dragi\u0107]], who he met at age 7 and has been cited as his mentor and friend.<ref name=\"dragic\">{{cite web |last1=Schmitz |first1=Mike |title=How Goran Dragic went from national hero to first-time All-Star |url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/22444031/how-miami-heat-guard-goran-dragic-went-national-hero-first-nba-all-star |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |date=February 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\nDon\u010di\u0107 was a member of the Slovenian squad for EuroBasket 2017, where his country won its first gold medal, after going undefeated (9\u20130) in the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2017/news/slovenia-overcome-injuries-to-claim-historic-title|title=Slovenia overcome injuries to claim historic title in Dragic's swansong|date=September 17, 2017|publisher=FIBA.basketball|accessdate=September 19, 2017}}</ref> In Slovenia's 103\u201397 win over [[Latvia national basketball team|Latvia]] in the quarterfinals, he scored 27 points and grabbed 9 rebounds.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2017/1209/Slovenia-Latvia|title=Slovenia v Latvia|date=September 12, 2017|publisher=FIBA.basketball|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> He recorded 11 points, 12 rebounds and 8 assists, in the 92\u201372 semi-final win over Spain.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2017/1409/Spain-Slovenia#tab=boxscore_statistics|title=Spain v Slovenia|publisher=FIBA.basketball|date=September 14, 2017|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> In the final, which Slovenia won by a score of 93\u201385 over Serbia, he had 8 points and 7 rebounds, before falling out of the game, due to an injury, in the game's third quarter.<ref>{{Cite news |url= http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2017/1709/Slovenia-Serbia#%7Ctab=boxscore_statistics |title= Slovenia v Serbia |date= September 19, 2017 |publisher= FIBA.basketball|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 was also named to the competition's [[FIBA EuroBasket All-Tournament Team|All-Tournament Team]], joining teammate Goran Dragi\u0107, who was also voted the [[EuroBasket MVP]].<ref>{{Cite news |url= http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2017/news/title-hero-dragic-caps-off-fairy-tale-finish-with-mvp-honors |title= Title hero Dragic caps off fairy tale finish with MVP honors |date= September 17, 2017 |publisher= FIBA.basketball|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Player profile==\n{{quote box\n|quote=\"[Don\u010di\u0107 is] incredible with the ball for a big guy. He's unbelievable in [[pick and roll]] play. His court vision is already unbelievable. I couldn't believe what I saw from a 19/20-year-old. He's a good shooter when he has time and I think he's going to be great for [the [[Dallas Mavericks]]] for a long, long time... I could shoot a little bit but I never had the court vision... the savviness that he brings to the game... He's going to pick defenses apart and it's going to be fun to watch.\"\n|source=\u2014 Mavericks star and teammate [[Dirk Nowitzki]] on Don\u010di\u0107 before the 2018\u201319 NBA season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lund |first1=Spencer |title=Dirk Nowitzki Says Teenage Luka Doncic Was Better Than He Was as a Teenager |url=https://www.complex.com/sports/2018/09/dirk-nowitzki-says-teenage-luka-doncic-better-than-him-as-teenager |website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]] |accessdate=October 6, 2018 |date=September 12, 2018}}</ref>\n|width=30em\n|align=right}}\nDon\u010di\u0107 has frequently been described as a \"position-less guard\" with attributes of a [[point guard]], [[shooting guard]], and [[small forward]].<ref name=\"kings\">{{cite web |last1=Ramirez |first1=Jordan |title=Get to Know: Luka Doncic |url=https://www.nba.com/kings/blog/get-know-luka-doncic |publisher=[[National Basketball Association]] |accessdate=June 10, 2018 |date=May 26, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Phillips |first1=Ryan |title=5 Things To Know About Luka Doncic |url=https://thebiglead.com/2018/06/21/luka-doncic-2018-nba-draft-five-things/ |publisher=The Big Lead |accessdate=October 5, 2018 |date=June 21, 2018}}</ref> Standing {{convert|6|ft|7|in|m|2}} and weighing {{convert|230|lbs|kg|1}},<ref>{{cite web|title=Luka Doncic|publisher=National Basketball Association|url=https://www.nba.com/players/luka/doncic/1629029|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref> he has been praised for his exceptional size and strength for the [[guard (basketball)|guard]] position.<ref name=\"austingreen\">{{cite news |last1=Green |first1=Austin |title=What you need to know about Luka Doncic, the most polished European teen prospect ever |url=https://www.cbssports.com/nba/news/2018-nba-draft-what-you-need-to-know-about-luka-doncic-the-most-polished-european-teen-prospect-ever/ |work=[[CBSSports.com|CBS Sports]] |accessdate=June 10, 2018 |date=June 5, 2018}}</ref> Dallas Mavericks executive [[Donnie Nelson]] lauded his \"[[point forward]] ability,\"<ref name=\"sefko\">{{cite web |last1=Sefko |first1=Eddie |title=Did the Mavericks draft a '6\u20137 Steve Nash' in Luka Doncic? |url=https://sportsday.dallasnews.com/dallas-mavericks/mavericks/2018/07/07/meet-theslovenian-teenager-mavs-draft-radar-drawing-nash-andporzingis-comparisons |website=[[The Dallas Morning News]] |accessdate=October 5, 2018 |date=July 7, 2018}}</ref> and sports website [[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] labeled him a \"legitimate point guard with the size of a [[Small ball (basketball)|small-ball]] [[power forward (basketball)|power forward]].\"<ref name=\"wonderyears\">{{cite web |last1=Tjarks |first1=Jonathan |title=The Mavericks\u2019 Wonder Years Are Here |url=https://www.theringer.com/nba/2018/6/22/17494086/luka-doncic-dallas-mavericks-nba-draft |publisher=[[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] |accessdate=October 5, 2018 |date=June 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSince his early years with Real Madrid, Don\u010di\u0107 was tabbed as one of Europe's premier talents, with Spanish newspaper ''[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]'' giving him the nickname \"El Ni\u00f1o Maravilla\" (Wonder Boy).<ref name=\"FIBA Article\"/> Entering the 2018 NBA draft, he was widely seen as one of the best and most accomplished European prospects of his generation.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tjarks |first1=Jonathan |title=Luka Doncic Might Be the Best European NBA Prospect of the 21st Century |url=https://www.theringer.com/2017/7/20/16077958/nba-draft-luka-doncic-real-madrid-f534e7428bf6 |publisher=[[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] |accessdate=July 2, 2018 |date=July 20, 2017}}</ref> ''[[Slam (magazine)|Slam]]'' magazine considered Don\u010di\u0107 the \"best international prospect ever,\"<ref name=\"slam\">{{cite web |last1=Laird |first1=Sam |title=Luka Doncic is the Best International Prospect Ever |url=https://www.slamonline.com/nba/luka-doncic-slam-cover/ |website=[[Slam (magazine)|Slam]] |accessdate=June 5, 2018 |date=May 15, 2018}}</ref> and sports website [[SB Nation]] called him \"most accomplished NBA prospect in decades.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ellentuck |first1=Matt |title=Luka Doncic is the most accomplished NBA prospect in decades. Congratulations, Mavericks fans |url=https://www.sbnation.com/nba/2018/6/21/17480374/nba-draft-2018-teamname-luka-doncic |publisher=[[SB Nation]] |accessdate=July 2, 2018 |date=June 21, 2018}}</ref> An anonymous NBA veteran scouting executive said that his game was \"leap years above anyone\" else in his draft class.<ref name=leapyears>{{cite web |last1=Wasserman |first1=Jonathan |title=NBA Exec Says Luka Doncic 'Leap Years Above Anyone' After EuroBasket Brilliance |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2732792-nba-exec-says-luka-doncic-leap-years-above-anyone-after-eurobasket-brilliance#slide2 |website=[[Bleacher Report]] |accessdate=June 10, 2018 |date=September 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\nDon\u010di\u0107 is versatile on the offensive end, displaying proficiency in shooting three-pointers and mid-range [[Jump shot (basketball)|jump shots]] as well as [[Basketball moves#Tear drop|floaters]] and shots in the post.<ref name=hawks>{{cite web |title=Will Luka Doncic Take The NBA By Storm? |url=http://www.nba.com/hawks/draft-profile-luka-doncic |publisher=[[National Basketball Association]] |accessdate=June 10, 2018 |date=June 6, 2018}}</ref> His basketball IQ, intangibles, and skills have been considered his primary assets, and he is seen as an elite facilitator, especially on the [[pick and roll]].<ref name=leapyears/> NBA and EuroLeague coach [[Ettore Messina]] called him \"phenomenal, especially mentally\" for his age.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zachari |first1=Antigoni |title=Ettore Messina: \"Luka Doncic is phenomenal, especially mentally\" |url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/nba-news/734293/ettore-messina-luka-doncic-is-phenomenal-especially-mentally/ |publisher=EuroHoops |accessdate=October 1, 2018 |date=September 6, 2018}}</ref> His lack of lateral quickness to stay in front most NBA point guards and wings has been labeled as one of his main flaws as a player.<ref name=fraschilla/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Green |first1=Austin |title=Luka Doncic scouting report: What to know about 2018 NBA Draft's top European prospect |url=https://www.cbssports.com/nba/news/luka-doncic-scouting-report-what-to-know-about-2018-nba-drafts-top-european-prospect/ |publisher=[[CBS Sports]] |accessdate=October 5, 2018 |date=June 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Woo |first1=Jeremy |title=Luka Doncic: Europe's Next Big Thing |url=https://www.si.com/nba/2017/08/10/luka-doncic-nba-draft-slovenia-real-madrid-eurobasket |website=[[Sports Illustrated]] |accessdate=October 5, 2018 |date=August 10, 2017}}</ref> Dallas Mavericks head coach [[Rick Carlisle]] refuted some of the worries regarding Don\u010di\u0107's athleticism, stating that \"for a 19-year-old, he's got a really unusual combination of size, speed, and deceptive quickness.\"<ref>https://www.eurohoops.net/en/nba-news/767584/rick-carlisle-on-what-has-impressed-him-the-most-about-luka-doncic/</ref> By his sophomore year, Lukas' ability to accelerate off a pick and blow by defenders to get to the basket is seen as one of his strengths.<ref>https://www.cbssports.com/nba/news/numbers-dont-lie-luka-doncics-historic-sophomore-season-is-second-to-none-in-the-nbas-modern-era/</ref>\n\nPrior to his draft, basketball journalist and scout, Austin Green, compared Don\u010di\u0107 to NBA players [[Paul Pierce]] and [[Joe Johnson (basketball)|Joe Johnson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/hawks/draft-profile-luka-doncic |title=Draft Profile: Will Luka Doncic Take The NBA By Storm? |publisher=National Basketball Association |date=June 8, 2018|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> Don\u010di\u0107 compared himself to [[Ben Simmons]] due to his versatility.<ref name=\"kimes\">{{cite web |last1=Kimes |first1=Mina |title=Luka Doncic Is No Darko Milicic |url=http://www.espn.com/espn/feature/story/_/id/23051130/will-luka-doncic-next-star-nba-player-europe |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=June 10, 2018 |date=April 9, 2018}}</ref> In his second season, LA Clippers coach, [[Doc Rivers]], when asked about Don\u010di\u0107 stated that \"there's a lot of people in him.\" He likened Don\u010di\u0107\u2019s stepback 3-pointers to [[James Harden]], his passing ability to [[Larry Bird]] and his court vision to [[LeBron James]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Townsend |first1=Brad |title=Does Luka Doncic have one true comparison? Mavs star evokes NBA greats past and present while showing \u2018he\u2019s an original\u2019 |url=https://www.dallasnews.com/sports/mavericks/2019/12/13/does-luka-doncic-have-one-true-comparison-mavs-star-is-evoking-nba-greats-past-and-present-while-showing-hes-an-original/ |publisher=dallasnews.com |date=13 December 2019}}</ref> NBA analyst, [[Kendrick Perkins]], called him \"baby LeBron\" due to his overall skill and dominance on the court.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Buford |first1=Landon |title=Mavs\u2019 Luka Doncic Is a \u2018Baby LeBron\u2019 Says NBA Champion |url=https://heavy.com/sports/2019/12/mavericks-luka-doncic-baby-lebron-nba/ |publisher=Heavy.com |date=17 December 2019}}</ref> In December 2019, San Antonio Spurs coach, [[Gregg Popovich]], called Don\u010di\u0107's playing style \"[[Magic Johnson]]-like\" because \"he sees the floor in that same way.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mutoni |first1=Marcel |title=Gregg Popovich: Luka Doncic \u2018Magic Johnson-Like\u2019 |url=https://www.slamonline.com/nba/gregg-popovich-luka-doncic-magic-johnson-like/ |publisher=SLAM |accessdate=28 December 2019 |date=27 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{Euroleague player statistics legend}}\n\n===EuroLeague===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#AFE6BA; width:3em;\"|\u2020\n|Denotes season in which Don\u010di\u0107's team won the [[EuroLeague champion|EuroLeague]]\n|-\n|style=\"background:#CFECEC; width:1em\"|\n|Led the league\n|}\n\n{{Euroleague player statistics start}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2015\u201316 Euroleague|2015\u201316]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2015\u201316 Real Madrid Baloncesto season|Real Madrid]]\n| 12 || 0 || 11.1 || .407 || .313 || '''.882''' || 2.3 || 2.0 || .2 || '''.3''' || 3.5 || 6.2\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2016\u201317 EuroLeague|2016\u201317]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2016\u201317 Real Madrid Baloncesto season|Real Madrid]]\n| '''35''' || 15 || 19.9 || .433 || '''.371 || .844 || 4.5 || 4.2 || .9 || .2 || 7.8 || 13.3\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;background:#AFE6BA;\"| [[2017\u201318 EuroLeague|2017\u201318]]\u2020\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2017\u201318 Real Madrid Baloncesto season|Real Madrid]]\n| 33 || '''17''' || '''25.9''' || '''.451''' || .329 || .816 || '''4.8''' || '''4.3''' || '''1.1''' || '''.3''' || '''16.0''' || style=\"background:#cfecec;\"|'''21.5'''\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"| Career\n| 80 || 32 || 21.0 || .443 || .344 || .828 || 4.3 || 3.9 || .9 || .3 || 10.6 || 15.6\n{{S-end}}\n\n===Liga ACB===\n:''Cited from ACB.com''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acb.com/stsacumjug.php?cod_jugador=460|title=Historial estad\u00edstico Doncic, Luka|language=Spanish|website=Liga ACB|acces