ription|1973 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Black Holiday\n| image          = Villeggiatura adalberto maria merli marco leto 006 jpg circ.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Marco Leto]]\n| producer       = [[Enzo Giulioli]]\n| writer         = [[Lino Del Fra]]<br>[[Marco Leto]]<br>[[Cecilia Mangini]]\n| narrator       =\n| starring       = [[Adolfo Celi]]\n| music          =[[Egisto Macchi]]\n| cinematography = Volfango Alfi\n| editing        = Giuseppe Giacobino\n| distributor    =\n| released       = {{film date|1973|11|13|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 112 minutes\n| country        = Italy\n| language       = Italian\n| budget         =\n}}\n'''''Black Holiday''''' ({{lang-it|'''La villeggiatura'''}}) is a 1973 Italian [[Political cinema|political]] [[drama film]] directed by [[Marco Leto]] and starring [[Adolfo Celi]].<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/124037/La-Villeggiatura/overview |title=New York Times: Black Holiday |accessdate=2008-08-31|work=NY Times}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Adolfo Celi]] as Commissioner Rizzuto\n* [[Adalberto Maria Merli]] as Franco Rossini\n* [[John Steiner]] as Scagnetti\n* [[Luigi Uzzo]] as Massanesi\n* [[Aldo De Correllis]] as Prisoner\n* [[Gianfranco Barra]] as Priest\n* [[Silvio Anselmo]] as Inventor\n* [[Vito Cipolla]] as Renzetti\n* [[Roberto Herlitzka]] as Guasco\n* [[Biagio Pelligra]] as Mastrodonato\n* [[Giuliano Petrelli]] as Nino\n* [[Nello Rivi\u00e8]] as Prisoner\n* [[Milena Vukotic]] as Daria Rossini\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Imdb title|id=0070881|title=Black Holiday}}\n\n[[Category:1973 films]]\n[[Category:Italian films]]\n[[Category:Italian-language films]]\n[[Category:1970s political drama films]]\n[[Category:1973 directorial debut films]]\n\n\n{{1970s-Italy-film-stub}}\n{{1970s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia