{"title_page": "Metro Tezoz\u00f3moc", "text_new": "{{short description|Mexico City metro station}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name            = [[File:Metro Tezoz\u00f3moc pictogram.svg|25px]] Tezoz\u00f3moc\n| style           = Mexico City Metro\n| style2          = 6\n| type            = [[Mexico City Metro|STC]] [[rapid transit]]\n| image           = Anden Tezozomoc tren.jpg\n| image_caption   =\n| address         = Av. Sauces and Ahuehuetes<br>Colonia Pasteros, [[Azcapotzalco]]\n| borough         = [[Mexico City]]\n| country         = Mexico\n| coordinates     = {{coord|19.495116|-99.196286|region:MX-DIF|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| line            = {{rint|mexicocity|6}}\n| structure       = Underground\n| platform        = 2 side platforms\n| levels          = 1\n| tracks          = 2\n| parking         = No\n| bicycle         = No\n| ADA             = No\n| opened          = 21 December 1983\n| services        = \n{{s-rail|title=Mexico City Metro}}\n{{s-line|system=Mexico City Metro|line=6|previous=El Rosario|next=Azcapotzalco}}\n| map_locator     = \n}}\n'''Metro Tezoz\u00f3moc''' is a [[rapid transit|metro]] station on Mexico's [[Mexico City Metro Line 6|Line 6]]. It is located in the  [[Azcapotzalco]] [[Municipalities of Mexico City|municipality]]. In 2019, the station had an average ridership of 5,738 passengers per day.<ref>{{cite web|title=Afluencia de estaci\u00f3n por l\u00ednea 2019|url=https://metro.cdmx.gob.mx/afluencia-de-estacion-por-linea-2019|publisher=Metro CDMX|access-date=3 April 2020|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Name and pictogram==\nThe station's pictogram depicts [[Tezozomoc (Azcapotzalco)|King Tezoz\u00f3moc]], who ruled the [[Azcapotzalco (altepetl)|Azcapotzalco altepetl]] for 80 years and it is also named in his honor.<ref>{{cite web|title= Tezoz\u00f3moc|url=https://metro.cdmx.gob.mx/la-red/linea-6/tezozomoc|publisher=Metro CDMX|access-date=3 April 2020|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==General information==\nThe station can be accessed through Ahuehuetes and Avenida Sauces Colonia Pasteros, in the [[Azcapotzalco]] borough. It has no underground direct connections, which means that, in order to exchange platforms, one has to exit the station and cross the street, thus making it necessary to pay the fare again, or reach one of the two neighboring stations and change platforms there (without paying extra), a feature only shared with [[Metro Allende]] in Line 2.<ref>[http://www.metro.df.gob.mx/red/estacion.html?id=83 Inauguraciones por orgen cronol\u00f3gico, longitudes de la l\u00ednea, estaciones, correspondencias, estaciones elevadas, a\u00e9reas y subterr\u00e1neas, afluencias, logotipos del Metro, icono ...<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080618161512/http://www.metro.df.gob.mx/red/estacion.html?id=83 |date=2008-06-18 }}</ref>\n\n==Exits==\n*North: Ahuehuetes street and Avenida Sauces, Colonia Pasteros\n*South: Ahuehuetes street and Avenida Sauces, Colonia Pasteros\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nImage:Metro Tezozomoc 01.jpg|Entrance sign\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* {{commonscat-inline|Tezoz\u00f3moc (station)}}\n\n{{MxMetro6}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Metro Tezozomoc}}\n[[Category:Mexico City metro stations|Tezozomoc]]\n\n\n{{Mexico-metro-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mexico City metro station}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name            = [[File:Metro Tezoz\u00f3moc pictogram.svg|25px]] Tezoz\u00f3moc\n| style           = Mexico City Metro\n| style2          = 6\n| type            = [[Mexico City Metro|STC]] [[rapid transit]]\n| image           = Anden Tezozomoc tren.jpg\n| image_caption   =\n| address         = Av. Sauces and Ahuehuetes<br>Colonia Pasteros, [[Azcapotzalco]]\n| borough         = [[Mexico City]]\n| country         = Mexico\n| coordinates     = {{coord|19.495116|-99.196286|region:MX-DIF|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| line            = {{rint|mexicocity|6}}\n| structure       = Underground\n| platform        = 2 side platforms\n| levels          = 1\n| tracks          = 2\n| parking         = No\n| bicycle         = No\n| ADA             = No\n| opened          = 21 December 1983\n| services        = \n{{s-rail|title=Mexico City Metro}}\n{{s-line|system=Mexico City Metro|line=6|previous=El Rosario|next=Azcapotzalco}}\n| map_locator     = \n}}\n'''Metro Tezoz\u00f3moc''' is a [[rapid transit|metro]] station on Mexico's [[Mexico City Metro Line 6|Line 6]]. It is located in the  [[Azcapotzalco]] [[Municipalities of Mexico City|municipality]]. In 2019, the station had an average ridership of 5,738 passengers per day, making it the busiest station in Line 7 and the 15th busiest station in the network.<ref>{{cite web|title=Afluencia de estaci\u00f3n por l\u00ednea 2019|url=https://metro.cdmx.gob.mx/afluencia-de-estacion-por-linea-2019|publisher=Metro CDMX|access-date=3 April 2020|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Name and pictogram==\nThe station's pictogram depicts [[Tezozomoc (Azcapotzalco)|King Tezoz\u00f3moc]], who ruled the [[Azcapotzalco (altepetl)|Azcapotzalco altepetl]] for 80 years and it is also named in his honor.<ref>{{cite web|title= Tezoz\u00f3moc|url=https://metro.cdmx.gob.mx/la-red/linea-6/tezozomoc|publisher=Metro CDMX|access-date=3 April 2020|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==General information==\nThe station can be accessed through Ahuehuetes and Avenida Sauces Colonia Pasteros, in the [[Azcapotzalco]] borough. It has no underground direct connections, which means that, in order to exchange platforms, one has to exit the station and cross the street, thus making it necessary to pay the fare again, or reach one of the two neighboring stations and change platforms there (without paying extra), a feature only shared with [[Metro Allende]] in Line 2.<ref>[http://www.metro.df.gob.mx/red/estacion.html?id=83 Inauguraciones por orgen cronol\u00f3gico, longitudes de la l\u00ednea, estaciones, correspondencias, estaciones elevadas, a\u00e9reas y subterr