{"title_page": "Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)", "text_new": "{{short description|2015 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)\n| image          = Bang Gang (une histoire d'amour moderne).jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Eva Husson]]\n| producers      = {{ubl|Didar Domehri|Laurent Baudens|Ga\u00ebl Nouaille}}\n| writer         = Eva Husson\n| starring       = [[Finnegan Oldfield]]\n| music          = [[White Sea (band)|White Sea]]\n| cinematography = Mattias Troelstrup\n| editing        = Emilie Orsini\n| distributor    = Ad Vitam Distribution\n| released       = {{Film date|2015|08|26|Festival du Film Francophone d'Angoul\u00eame|2016|01|13|France|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 98 minutes\n| country        = France\n| language       = French\n| budget         = $2.3 million\n| gross          = $220,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jpbox-office.com/fichfilm.php?id=15678|title=Bang Gang (une histoire d\\'amour moderne) (2016)- JPBox-Office|publisher=|accessdate=23 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Italic title|noerror|all=yes}}\n'''''Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)''''' ({{lang-fr|'''Bang Gang (une histoire d'amour moderne)'''}}) is a French [[drama film]] directed by Eva Husson. It was shown in the Platform section of the [[2015 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/toronto-international-film-festival-announces-inaugural-platform-lineup-including-world-premiere-of-ben-wheatleys-high-rise-20150813 |title=Toronto International Film Festival Announces Inaugural Platform Lineup |accessdate=14 August 2015 |work=IndieWire}}</ref> It is Husson's directorial debut.\n\n==Plot==\nIn [[Biarritz]], teenager Alex temporarily lives alone (and later with his best friend Nikita) while his mother is abroad for work. In his house he organizes [[sex parties]] (called ''bang gangs'') with other teenagers, also including [[recreational drug use]]. Videos of the parties are posted on a password-protected website. The girl George and her best friend Laetitia are active participants of the parties.  George does not like that Laetitia has sex with Alex, with whom George had sex first. Gabriel does not like to attend the parties at first, but finally goes to one to have sex with George, in a separate room. [[Sexually transmitted infection]]s, a [[teenage pregnancy]] and unintended posting of the videos on [[YouTube]] make the parties known to parents and other authorities, after which they are discontinued. Gabriel and George are concerned about publicized sex videos of George. Gabriel finds the boy who posted them and forces him to remove them. The infections are easily treated. The pregnant girl has an [[abortion]]. George and Gabriel start a regular relationship.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Finnegan Oldfield]] as Alex\n* [[Marilyn Lima]] as George\n* [[Daisy Broom]] as Laetitia\n* [[Fred Hotier]] as Nikita\n* [[Lorenzo Lefebvre]] as Gabriel\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe film received mixed reviews by critics. Review aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reports that 67% of 27 critics gave the film a positive review, for an average rating of 6/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bang_gang|title=Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)|date=1 April 2005|work=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=26 November 2016}}</ref> Review aggregate [[Metacritic]] gave the film a score of 53 out of 100, based on 13 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/bang-gang-a-modern-love-story|title=Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)|work=Metacritic|accessdate=26 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Recipient !! Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 2015\n| Les Arcs European Film Festival \n| Crystal Arrow\n| rowspan=3|Eva Husson \n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[BFI London Film Festival]]\n| First Feature Competition\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Toronto International Film Festival]]\n| Platform Prize\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3838728|Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|bang_gang}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bang Gang A Modern Love Story}}\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:French-language films]]\n[[Category:2015 directorial debut films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2015 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)\n| image          = Bang Gang (une histoire d'amour moderne).jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Eva Husson]]\n| producers      = {{ubl|Didar Domehri|Laurent Baudens|Ga\u00ebl Nouaille}}\n| writer         = Eva Husson\n| starring       = [[Finnegan Oldfield]]\n| music          = [[White Sea (band)|White Sea]]\n| cinematography = Mattias Troelstrup\n| editing        = Emilie Orsini\n| distributor    = Ad Vitam Distribution\n| released       = {{Film date|2015|08|26|Festival du Film Francophone d'Angoul\u00eame|2016|01|13|France|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 98 minutes\n| country        = France\n| language       = French\n| budget         = $2.3 million\n| gross          = $220,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jpbox-office.com/fichfilm.php?id=15678|title=Bang Gang (une histoire d\\'amour moderne) (2016)- JPBox-Office|publisher=|accessdate=23 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Italic title|noerror|all=yes}}\n'''''Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)''''' ({{lang-fr|'''Bang Gang (une histoire d'amour moderne)'''}}) is a French [[drama film]] directed by Eva Husson. It was shown in the Platform section of the [[2015 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/toronto-international-film-festival-announces-inaugural-platform-lineup-including-world-premiere-of-ben-wheatleys-high-rise-20150813 |title=Toronto International Film Festival Announces Inaugural Platform Lineup |accessdate=14 August 2015 |work=IndieWire}}</ref> It is Husson's directorial debut.\n\n==Plot==\nIn [[Biarritz]], teenager Alex temporarily lives alone (and later with his best friend Nikita) while his mother is abroad for work. In his house he organizes [[sex parties]] (called ''bang gangs'') with other teenagers, also including [[recreational drug use]]. Videos of the parties are posted on a password-protected website. The girl George and her best friend Laetitia are active participants of the parties.  George does not like that Laetitia has sex with Alex, with whom George had sex first. Gabriel does not like to attend the parties at first, but finally goes to one to have sex with George, in a separate room. [[Sexually transmitted infection]]s, a [[teenage pregnancy]] and unintended posting of the videos on [[YouTube]] make the parties known to parents and other authorities, after which they are discontinued. Gabriel and George are concerned about publicized sex videos of George. Gabriel finds the boy who posted them and forces him to remove them. The infections are easily treated. The pregnant girl has an [[abortion]]. George and Gabriel start a regular relationship.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Finnegan Oldfield]] as Alex\n* [[Marilyn Lima]] as George\n* [[Daisy Broom]] as Laetitia\n* [[Fred Hotier]] as Nikita\n* [[Lorenzo Lefebvre]] as Gabriel\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe film received mixed reviews by critics. Review aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reports that 67% of 27 critics gave the film a positive review, for an average rating of 6/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bang_gang|title=Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)|date=1 April 2005|work=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=26 November 2016}}</ref> Review aggregate [[Metacritic]] gave the film a score of 53 out of 100, based on 13 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/bang-gang-a-modern-love-story|title=Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)|work=Metacritic|accessdate=26 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Recipient !! Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| 2015\n| Les Arcs European Film Festival \n| Crystal Arrow\n| rowspan=3|Eva Husson \n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[BFI London Film Festival]]\n| First Feature Competition\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Toronto International Film Festival]]\n| Platform Prize\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3838728|Bang Gang (A Modern Love Story)}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|bang_gang}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bang Gang A Modern Love Story}}\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:French-language films]]\n[[Category:2015 directorial debut films]]\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bang_Gang_(A_Modern_Love_Story)"}
